wholesome /ˈhəʊlsəm/

1. ADJ If you describe something as wholesome , you approve of it because you think it is likely to have a positive influence on people's behaviour or mental state, especially because it does not involve anything sexually immoral. 有益身心的 (尤指不涉及非道德的性内容) [表赞许] 

例： The Dove Foundation aims to promote wholesome family entertainment. 达夫基金会旨在倡导有益身心的家庭娱乐。 

2. ADJ If you describe food as wholesome , you approve of it because you think it is good for your health. (食物) 有益健康的 [表赞许] 

例： ...fresh, wholesome ingredients. …有益健康的新鲜配料。

</div>

